Articles.Content: Please read the Stock Support & Bug Reporting Guide and post the requested information. The output_log.txt is much more useful than the error.log, and it would help to know which version of Windows you're running.
Sorry, I just looked a little deeper into the output logs and found out that it was a memory (RAM) issue.
